  "instructions": [
    "in a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the short ribs over medium-high heat until browned on all sides.",
    "remove the browned ribs from the pot and set aside.",
    "add the mirepoix to the pot and cook until the vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the turnips, parsnips, salt, and pepper to the pot and cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "add the water to the pot and bring to a boil.",
    "return the short ribs to the pot and reduce the heat to low.",
    "simmer the stew for 2 hours, or until the meat is tender and falling off the bone.",
    "remove the pot from the heat and stir in the black treacle, browning sauce, allspice, and cinnamon.",
    "stir in the butter until melted.",
    "serve the stew hot, garnished with chopped parsley.",
    "if desired, serve with crusty bread or over mashed potatoes."
  ],
